CONCLUSIONS: Selection bias explaining some of the results cannot be excluded. 
However, NFPA patients with GHRT had reduced overall mortality compared with the 
general population, and death due to malignancy was not increased. This suggests 
that long-term GHRT is safe in adult patients selected for treatment.

